SIMPLE: internuncio
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Internuncio
<hw>In`ter*nun"ci*o</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Internuncios</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>internuntius</ets>; <ets>inter</ets> between + <ets>nuntius</ets>,
<ets>nuncius</ets>, messenger: cf. It. <ets>internunzio</ets>. See
<er>Nuncio</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A messenger between two parties.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A representative, or charg⟦eacute⟧ d'affaires, of
the pope at a foreign court or seat of government, ranking next below a
nuncio.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This title was formerly given also to the Austrian envoy
at Constantinople.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Internuncioship</ent>⟦br⟧
